What Is It ?
============
Package kz, named after its creator, Karel Zimmer, contains scripts for
installing and managing Red Hat and Red Hat-based systems such as Rocky Linux.

Also installs (dependencies)
============================
epel-release    - Extra Packages for Enterprise Linux (EPEL)
newt            - Display dialog boxes from shell scripts (e.g. whiptail TUI)
psmisc          - Identify processes using files with fuser
python3         - Interactive high-level object-oriented language
python3-systemd - Use systemd.journal module for Python
rsync           - File-copying tool to backup and restore files

How To Use
==========
For how to use this package see Checklist installation.
Checklist installation can be found on the site https://karelzimmer.nl/en,
under Linux.

